CONTRACTOR SAFETY: 
The Riverbank Terminal uses contractors during periods of increased maintenance or construction activities. The Kiva Energy evaluates and qualifies contractors who will work on the systems and equipment. Riverbank Terminal has procedures in place to ensure that contractors:

~ perform their work in a safe manner;
~ have appropriate knowledge and skills;
~ are aware of the hazards of their workplace;
~ understand what they should do in the event of an emergency;
~ understand and follow site specific safety rules; and
~ inform plant personnel of hazards that they find while performing their work.

Effective implementation of the contractor safety program is accomplished by providing contractors with an orientation session that covers 
(1) a process overview, 
(2) information about the safety and health hazards, 
(3) emergency response plan requirements and 
(4) safe work practices prior to beginning their work.

Formalized contractor safety procedures have been implemented at the Riverbank Terminal. Riverbank Terminal management staff will conduct periodic reviews of the contractor safety performance after program implementation.

LPG REGULATORY FRAMEWORK: 
The Facility implements the provisions of the following guidelines and regulations for this regulated substance. The California Code of Regulations Title 8 provide the regulatory framework for the design of equipment and use of LPG gas. The National Fire Protection Code (NFPA) 58, LP-Gas Code is incorporated by reference in Title 8, Section 450. The NFPA 58 standard is supplemented by additional regulations in Title 8 Sections 470 through 494.
